<subSubSection id="8D7D508C90987D700453ABFFF4FC48F3" lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="66CCEBCEC166166E9A0E9BF1E02D4D7F" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D7705334ECCA933E21680CEB24F15FFD" lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
(Figure 
<figureCitation id="C876E35CEBFEABA50105F9E28AF8B828" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Distribution of Solanum interius Rydb." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.123.31738.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/305322" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">23</figureCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName id="0119555D784C149C91C36479B3887BC4" authorityName="Rydb., Bull. Torrey Bot. Club 31: 641. 1905 [&quot;" authorityYear="1904" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum interius" order="Solanales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="interius">
<emphasis id="9E2A0DB143D5EDCC426A99DFD9FE4162" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Solanum interius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to North America, and the most common species of morelloid in the Great Plains. It is less common west of the Rocky Mountains, and although it does extend to Arizona and western New Mexico, 
<taxonomicName id="F4F65DFA2A9AB5307A530FADB925CFB6" family="Verbenaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. interius" order="Solanales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="interius">
<emphasis id="C5EB0F1C8DEB343A6C5E0A0AA54F6E86" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<pageBreakToken id="0AD96E8C61062AB0BC48D1F5FCF2A8B1" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" start="start">S</pageBreakToken>
. interius
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not occur on the Gulf Coast where it is replaced by 
<taxonomicName id="557847E3376E60F143B853F0BAA9E052" family="Verbenaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. nigrescens" order="Solanales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="nigrescens">
<emphasis id="9FBBB78EE571C83635D1FA12B9EF8336" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">S. nigrescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Records of 
<taxonomicName id="3125867C862F702CC81FD340B44C6A4A" family="Verbenaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. interius" order="Solanales" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="interius">
<emphasis id="8B3E7E211CAF1AE023328C42744EC928" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">S. interius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for Canada (Saskatchewan, 
<bibRefCitation id="E9F6D5C1ECD8DFF65CA95070A1F0E471" author="Harms, VL" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" refId="B103" refString="Harms, VL, 2006. Annotated catalogue of Saskatchewan vascular plants. Published by the author, Saskatoon." title="Annotated catalogue of Saskatchewan vascular plants. Published by the author, Saskatoon." year="2006">Harms 2006</bibRefCitation>
) have not been verified with voucher specimens, although it is to be expected there. Specimens annotated by Harms as 
